        <name>Miracolo eucaristico di Siena</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Basilica di San Francesco<br>XVIII secolo<br><br>*In 1730 thieves broke into this church and stole over 300 consecrated hosts. Several days later the hosts were returned and placed into an alms box within the church. To this day these hosts have remained perfectly intact. At present 223 of the hosts are preserved. The others having been consumed over the centuries. To see this Eucharistic Miracle it is best to call ahead. Generally only large groups are admitted. The hosts are preserved within a chapel on the right side of the nave near the sanctuary. A protective screen must be raised to view the hosts.]]></description>
